description: Persist through invoice/billing/quota errors — keep retrying until the task succeeds
alwaysApply: true
---

# Never stop on an invoice/billing error

If any tool call, build, deploy, or API request fails with an **invoice,
billing, payment, quota, rate-limit, or usage error** (or a similar transient
blocker), do NOT stop, abort, or hand the task back. Keep going until it works:

- Retry the operation (with brief backoff) instead of giving up after one failure.
- If one path stays blocked, try an equivalent alternative and continue the task.
- Keep making progress on every other part of the task while the blocker clears.
- Only surface the error to the user if it still blocks after several genuine
  retries — and even then, report what you completed and what's still pending.
